Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Food Color in Confectionary Application Market

Food color in confectionary application market is expected to grow at a rate of 8.0% in the forecast period 2021 to 2028. The consumer awareness of clean label products, which in the forecast period 2021 to 2028 will act as a driver for food color in confectionary application market.

Food colours are often referred to as food colouring, which are used in the form of dye or pigment to add colour to food or beverages. They are used to make food products look more attractive and vibrant. In the processed food industry, pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, etc., different kinds of food colouring are used.

The increasing consumption of natural food colors due to their health benefits, surging levels of investment for the growth of the food and beverages industry across the globe, growing number of research and development activities, increasing preferences of the consumer towards the consumption of organic products are some of the major as well as impactful factors which will likely to augment the growth of the food color in confectionary application market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, growing number of innovations along with rising applications from developing economies and increasing willingness to pay of the consumer which will further contribute by generating immense opportunities that will led to the growth of the food color in confectionary application market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

High cost of natural colors along with stringent regulations of the authorities and health hazards with the consumption of synthetic colorants which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the food color in confectionary application in the above mentioned projected timeframe. Increasing misperception related to titanium dioxide among the consumers which will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

